Get default equations of each type.

Source: R/get_equations.R
get_equations.Rd

Get default equations of each type.

get_equations(dbh_species)

Arguments

dbh_species

A dataframe as those created with census_species().

Value

A nested dataframe with each row containing the data of an equation type.

See also

Other functions to manipulate equations: evaluate_equations, pick_best_equations

Examples

census <- allodb::scbi_tree1
species <- allodb::scbi_species
dbh_species <- census_species(
  census, species,
  site = "scbi"
)

get_equations(dbh_species)
#> # A tibble: 5 x 2
#>   eqn_type       data                 
#>   <chr>          <list>               
#> 1 species        <tibble [8,930 x 8]> 
#> 2 genus          <tibble [5,642 x 8]> 
#> 3 mixed_hardwood <tibble [5,516 x 8]> 
#> 4 family         <tibble [10,141 x 8]>
#> 5 woody_species  <tibble [0 x 8]>
